%N A304050 Coordination sequence for one of the inner vertices introduced in the first inflation-deflation step in a Half-Hex tiling.
%C A304050 The first inflation-deflation step leads to the following configuration (where O marks the reference vertex for this sequence; this vertex is hexavalent from the second inflation-deflation step onwards):
%C A304050            +-------------+
%C A304050           / \           / \
%C A304050          /   \         /   \
%C A304050         /     O-------+     \
%C A304050        /     /         \     \
%C A304050       /     /           \     \
%C A304050      +-----+-------------+-----+
%C A304050 After k > 1 inflation-deflation steps, we can compute a finite coordination sequence c_k (until we reach the edge of the tiling after k steps). It appears that for i and j such that 1 < i < j, c_i is a prefix of c_j; this sequence is the limiting sequence of the { c_i, i > 1 } family.
%C A304050 See A304076 and A304077 for similar sequences.
